column5: Not sure if this was already posted here
Hard to believe the pigeons can't see the fish that close to them. There some smart fish!!
I find this fascinating the way they adapted to this new way of eating
Cool! Those pigeons must be pretty strong to get free...
Kinda reminds me of the killer whales and the seals.
Cool to see that cat fish act just like any other cat stalking a bird
I think their lucky to get away   Yep... they'll beach them selves to get to the food   Very true Mike!
Could very well be Christopher   Only thing missing is the treble hooks
Size 4.0 circle hook with half of a chicken hanging off of it or a 3lb sucker Get the camera ready too lol. Catfish have been around for thousands of years...i think they adapt well hahah.

mu grandpa was telling me stories about fishing for big cat fish, back in Europe, tying up the line with a big hook to a duckling and let it swim  I don't think cat fish are very smart, they just go for pretty much anything  killer whales yes, very very smart here's a little video if you haven't seen the whole documentary "Orca killing school"
http://m.youtube.com/#/watch?v=MhSqtbu_24M&desktop_uri=%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DMhSqtbu_24M  Musky eats chicken lol    Those catfish are awesome!
Nice, cant want for spring when those big cats start to spawn.
